description._content: Description: Ship-building: Work in Cayman Brac on a barge for the Turks Island salt industry. Location: Cayman Brac, Cayman Islands Date: 1957-1960 Description: Her Royal Highness The Princess Royal inspects a Guard of Honour of Sea Scouts at George Town on 22nd March, 1960. Location: George Town, Cayman Islands Date: 22 March 1960 Description: The Administrator presents the Members of the Executive Council to Her Royal Highness The Princess Royal - 22nd March, 1960. Location: Cayman Islands Date: 22 March 1960 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/304 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives, uploaded as part of the Caribbean Through a Lens project. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location. We need your help to fill in the gaps, to unearth the missing stories, the social and cultural memories from this selection of colonial recordings. Do you recognise anything or anyone in the photographs? Do they provoke any personal or historical memories? If so, please leave your comments, tags and stories to enrich our records. If you would like to get involved in our community project Caribbean through a lens, we would love to hear from you. For high quality reproductions of any item from our collection please contact our image library
